4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Legislature, by local
6 legislation, may abolish the office of constable in a
7 county.
8 This bill would authorize the Legislature, by
9 local legislation, to revise the number of constables
10 in the county, revise the areas within the county to be
11 represented by a constable, or revise the conditions
12 under which a constable vacates his or her office.
13 This bill would also make conforming changes.
14
15
16 A BILL
17 TO BE ENTITLED
18 AN ACT
19
20 Relating to constables; to authorize the Legislature to
21 further provide for the number of constables in the county;
22 and to further provide for conditions constitution a vacancy
23 in the office of constable.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. Sections 36-23-1, 36-23-3, and 36-23-7, Code
26 of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
27 "§36-23-1
28 (a) There shall be one constable for each election
Page 1

(a) There shall be one constable for each election
HB499 INTRODUCED
29 precinct in each county, to be elected as provided by law, who
30 shall hold office for four years from the first Monday after
31 the second Tuesday in January next after his election and
32 until his successor is elected and qualified.
33 (b) Any county, by local legislation, may abolish the
34 office of constable.
35 (c) Notwithstanding subsection (a), any county, by
36 local legislation, may do any of the following:
37 (1) Revise the number of constables in the county.
38 (2) Revise the areas within the county to be
39 represented by constables.
40 (3) Revise the conditions under which a constable is
41 considered to have vacated his or her office."
42 "§36-23-3
43 When a vacancy in any election precinct is occasioned
44 by the death or removal from such precinct of occurs in the
45 office of any constable thereof, the judge of probate must
46 shall notify the Governor."
47 "§36-23-7
48 The A constable shall vacate his or her office by
49 removal from the election precinct for which he or she is
50 elected, or as otherwise provided by law."
51 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
52 1, 2026.
